CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 17, 1962, pg. A5, reads: "Successful Round-Up - The annual 1962 membership enrollment of the Centre Avenue branch YMCA closed with the workers producing 85.5 per cent of their goal.  The workers above made the Hall of Fame by totaling 100 or more points.  Left to right, seated: Mrs. Dorcas Turner, Miss Lucile Wyant, J. D. Lewis, Mrs. Sarah Robinson, Miss Velva Boea.  Second row: William H. Coleman (seated, also highest ranch leader), and (standing) Jeese [Jesse] E. Bolden Jr., Frank Lavelle, John Young, Paul E. Thompson (also highest team captain), Laurence Washington and Robert Nicholas.  Third row: Beverly H. Hunt Sr., Andrew Frazier, Frank E. Bolden Jr. (also the highest individual producer), Wiliam [William] Albea, William A. Arvin, Rev. James B. Cayce, 'Big Boss' of the ranch organization; Atty. Byrd R. Brown, John H. Boykin Sr., and Mrs. James M. Burgette, who is missing from the picture."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue YMCA enrollment workers seated from left: Dorcas Turner, Lucile Wyant, J. D. Lewis, Sarah Robinson, Velva Boea; second row: William H. Coleman, Jesse E. Bolden Jr., Frank Lavelle, John Young, Paul E. Thompson, Laurence Washington, Robert Nicholas; third row: Beverly H. Hunt Sr., Andrew Frazier, Frank E. Bolden Jr., William Albea, William A. Arvin, Rev. James B. Cayce, Atty. Byrd R. Brown, and John H. Boykin Sr. posed under Henry O.Tanner painting "Christ and His Mother" in YMCA
